title: Establishes the canal pilot water level management program and hydraulic model
summary: Establishes the canal pilot water level management program and hydraulic model for the purpose of enhancing navigation and flood mitigation, improving real-time flood forecasting, enabling pro-active flood responsiveness and developing unified operating procedures through collection, analysis, coordination and dissemination of real-time water and systems data along the canal system; provides for a report to be issued within three years of the effective date.
actClause: AN ACT to amend the canal law, in relation to establishing the pilot water level management program and hydraulic model
